Sure! Here‚Äôs the updated ‚ÄúHow To‚Äù guide that includes the new flags and functionalities added to the projinit CLI tool.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ How to Set Up and Use projinit CLI (Cross-Platform Guide)

‚∏ª

üìÅ 1. Clone the project

git clone https://github.com/Martins-O/projinit.git



‚∏ª

üß∞ 2. Install pipx (if not installed)

macOS or Linux:

brew install pipx   # macOS

python3 -m pip install --user pipx

pipx ensurepath

Windows (via PowerShell):

python -m pip install --user pipx

pipx ensurepath

Restart your terminal after running pipx ensurepath.

‚∏ª

üöÄ 3. Install projinit using pipx

In the terminal, navigate to the root of your projinit project:

cd projinit

pipx install .

‚úÖ This makes the projinit command available globally.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ 4. Usage

Now you can run projinit from anywhere in your terminal:

projinit

It will prompt you to:
	‚Ä¢	Create a new project or use an existing one:
	‚Ä¢	New project: Asks for the project name, subfolders, etc.
	‚Ä¢	Existing project: Asks for the path and sets up the folders.
	‚Ä¢	Create a Python virtual environment (optional):
	‚Ä¢	You can skip this with the --no-venv flag.
	‚Ä¢	You can specify a Python version with the --python-version flag.
	‚Ä¢	Add dependencies to requirements.txt:
	‚Ä¢	Provide a comma-separated list of dependencies via the --dependencies flag.
	‚Ä¢	If no dependencies are provided, a preconfigured template for requirements.txt will be created.
	‚Ä¢	Initialize a Git repository (optional):
	‚Ä¢	You can choose to initialize a Git repo by answering y when prompted.
	‚Ä¢	If desired, add a remote repository URL with the --git-remote flag.
	‚Ä¢	Interactive Setup (optional):
	‚Ä¢	Enable an interactive setup where you will be prompted for custom folder names by using the --interactive flag.

Example usage with flags:

projinit --interactive --dependencies flask,requests --python-version 3.9 --git-remote https://github.com/your-repo.git



‚∏ª

üí° Notes
	‚Ä¢	To uninstall projinit:

pipx uninstall projinit

    ‚Ä¢	For more information, visit the project's GitHub repository: https://github.com/Martins-O/projinit
